We are runinng a free school in Shalimar Garden main named BAL VIKAAS KAREYKRAM for educating the slum children.We have more than 125 children. Also we are running 3 sewing machine training center for slum women.We have more than 57 women we as such donot get support from any one still we make best for our efforts to help these needy people.We are looking for more opportunities to work for the slum people.Our future plans include giving training to slum people on basics of computers basics of beauty parlour etc to make them earn and feel confident.

ngoList.detailsOfAchievement: Ace Vision was formed by a group of academicians and social workers in the year 2002 and formally got registered under the Societies Registration Act of 1860 on 18 July 2007 with the aim to work for issues related to Indian society, culture & heritage, minority rights, promote social concerns and further the objectives of secularism and nationalism in order to create a healthy and developed society and build India into a modern and vibrant nation. The organization worked for upholding and disseminating secular ideas and promoted research along nationalist lines in order to uncover facts and information that built objective and modern studies. It worked at grass root level for upliftment of interests of the sub-alterns and weaker sections of the society including women, children, dalits and minorities etc. It was attempted to narrow the socio-economic and intellectual gap in the society that helped in to usher an age of modernity, rationality and equality. With the accomplishments of these fundamental objectives, Ace Vision strove to forge greater work relations with likeminded institutions of national and international repute in furthering advancement of social, cultural and humanitarian concerns.
